[h1]v0.1.2 - Off-road floor + tire slip wear + stuck diagnostics[/h1]

[b]Off-road grip floor[/b] (Handling page, default 0.55, range 0.3-1.0). Stops sports-tire profiles from dropping off-road grip so low a high-HP car barely moves on grass. Bump it higher if you want even more "brute-force through the field" behaviour.

[b]Tires wear from wheel slip[/b] (Tires & Load page, default ON) + rate slider. When the engine is forcing wheels faster than the surface can grip (e.g. flooring it on grass), driven tires lose condition over time. Lets you push through low-grip surfaces at the cost of bald tires later. Set rate to 0 to disable wear without turning the model off.

Tightened the load-penalty clamp so even worst-case stacking with other mods can't drop force-to-wheels below 15% of nominal. Defensive against the "engine revving but car doesn't move" reports.

New diagnostic log [code][BVD-DIAG] stuck: ...[/code] fires once per stuck event with the load%, force, tyre and surface. If you've hit the stuck-car bug, please share a snippet of your DebugLog so we can pinpoint which multiplier is the culprit.

[b]Lua-only.[/b] No manual install update.
